      "message": "What\u0027s the benefit here to represent an object path with `std::string` if we already have a value type (`sdbusplus::message::object_path`) for it?\n\n\nIt\u0027s inconsistent with the code which is using sdbusplus. Most of that code is using object_path.\n\n`std::string` has quite a large API surface and most of that is not needed when dealing with object paths inside of sdbusplus.\n\nhttps://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/string/basic_string.html\n\nCleaning up this API can make the code more readable and more robust.",
